@NODE What " What is Blitz-Config"

Blitz-Config is a replacement for most of the options in the standard
'UserOptions' module supplied by DLG.

After seeing many users staring at the cluttered screen, I decided to write
this program.

Some features:

       o Not all functions on-screen at once.
       o Displays text instead of numbers where possible.
       o Bail-out on all changes made.

What it doesn't do:

       o Doesn't edit any of the newscan lists or global archive list.
       o Doesn't edit capture flags.
       o Doesn't edit character sets.
       o Doesn't edit last file/message area field.

@ENDNODE
@NODE setup " Setting up Blitz-Config"

Blitz-Config can take several parameters. Call it thus:

       Blitz-Config [-A -C -F -G -L -P -S -T -T"<template>"] [-U]

  Where:

       -A            : Edit address details.
       -C            : Change computer type.
       -F            : Edit transfer protocols.
       -G            : Edit general settings.
       -L            : Edit alias.
       -P            : Edit password.
       -S            : Edit screen settings.
       -T            : Edit phone number.
       -T"<template>": Edit phone number using a template.

                        ONE OF THE ABOVE MUST BE USED

All of the above switches are mutually exclusive!

<template> is used to format the phone number. Eg -T"(___) __-_____" is a
possible template. It must be enclosed in quotes!

       -U            : Allow lowercase letters for alias and address details.

This set-up allows you to have a user config menu, allowing users to edit
their settings in a more simple way, plus offer the standard issue
UserOptions menu as well.

@ENDNODE
@NODE status "Blitz-config status"

I have decided to release Blitz-Config as freeware.

@ENDNODE
